    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A twill or pile fabric with a raised nap on both sides. Originally made of wool, it is most often now made of cotton or other synthetic fibers, and often used as a light-absorbent cloth in theater or film productions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
